.TH "KOOPA" "1" "May 2026" "" ""
.
.SH "NAME"
\fBkoopa\fR \- shell bootloader for data science
.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBkoopa\fR \fIcommand\fR [options] [args\.\.\.]
.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
koopa is a shell bootloader for data science that manages installation, configuration, and updates of command\-line applications and libraries\.
.
.SH "GLOBAL OPTIONS"
.
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR, \fB\-h\fR
Show help\. Place after a command to view command\-specific help\.
.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR, \fB\-V\fR
Print version information\.
.
.TP
\fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose output\.
.
.SH "COMMANDS"
.
.SS "Package management"
.
.TP
\fBinstall\fR \fIapp\fR\.\.\.
Install one or more applications\.
.
.TP
\fBreinstall\fR \fIapp\fR\.\.\.
Reinstall applications, with optional reverse dependency rebuilds\.
.
.TP
\fBuninstall\fR [\fIapp\fR\.\.\.]
Remove installed applications\. Defaults to uninstalling koopa itself\.
.
.TP
\fBupdate\fR [\fIapp\fR\.\.\.]
Update applications to latest versions\. Defaults to updating koopa\.
.
.TP
\fBconfigure\fR \fIapp\fR\.\.\.
Run post\-install configuration for applications\.
.
.SS "Utility commands"
.
.TP
\fBapp\fR \fIsubcommand\fR
Application\-specific utilities (e\.g\. \fBkoopa app salmon quant\fR)\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem\fR \fIsubcommand\fR
System information, prefix lookups, and administration commands\.
.
.TP
\fBdevelop\fR \fIsubcommand\fR
Developer and maintenance utilities\.
.
.TP
\fBinternal\fR \fIsubcommand\fR
Internal low\-level utilities (not intended for direct use)\.
.
.TP
\fBversion\fR
Print koopa version\.
.
.TP
\fBheader\fR
Print path to the shell script header file, for use with \fBsource\fR\.
.
.TP
\fBinstall\-all\-apps\fR
Install all registered applications\.
.
.TP
\fBinstall\-default\-apps\fR
Install the default set of applications\.
.
.SH "INSTALL OPTIONS"
.
.TP
\fB\-\-bootstrap\fR
Bootstrap mode (minimal dependency resolution)\.
.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-dependencies\fR
Skip dependency installation\.
.
.TP
\fB\-\-private\fR
Install from private sources\.
.
.TP
\fB\-\-reinstall\fR
Force reinstall even if already installed\.
.
.TP
\fB\-\-system\fR
Install in system mode\.
.
.TP
\fB\-\-user\fR
Install in user mode\.
.
.TP
\fB\-D\fR \fIarg\fR
Pass additional arguments through to the installer\. Can be repeated\.
.
.SH "REINSTALL OPTIONS"
.
.TP
\fB\-\-all\-revdeps\fR
Reinstall the specified apps and all of their reverse dependencies\.
.
.TP
\fB\-\-only\-revdeps\fR
Reinstall only the reverse dependencies, not the specified apps\.
.
.SH "UNINSTALL / UPDATE / CONFIGURE OPTIONS"
.
.TP
\fB\-\-system\fR
Operate in system mode\.
.
.TP
\fB\-\-user\fR
Operate in user mode\.
.
.SH "SYSTEM SUBCOMMANDS"
.
.TP
\fBsystem check\fR
Run system dependency version checks\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem info\fR
Show system information\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem prefix\fR [\fIname\fR]
Print the installation prefix for koopa or a named application\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem version\fR \fIname\fR
Print the installed version of an application\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem which\fR \fIname\fR
Print the real path of an application\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem list\fR \fIsubcommand\fR
List system information\. Subcommands: \fBapp\-versions\fR, \fBdotfiles\fR, \fBlaunch\-agents\fR, \fBpath\-priority\fR, \fBprograms\fR\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem prune\-apps\fR
Remove stale application versions\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem update\-tex\-packages\fR
Update TeX Live packages via \fBtlmgr\fR\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem hostname\fR
Print the system hostname\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem os\-string\fR
Print the operating system identifier string\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem switch\-to\-develop\fR
Switch koopa installation to the development branch\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem test\fR
Run koopa test suite\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem delete\-cache\fR
Delete koopa cache files\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem enable\-passwordless\-sudo\fR
Enable passwordless sudo for the current user\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem disable\-passwordless\-sudo\fR
Disable passwordless sudo for the current user\.
.
.SS "macOS\-specific system subcommands"
.
.TP
\fBsystem clean\-launch\-services\fR
Clean the macOS Launch Services database\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem create\-dmg\fR
Create a DMG disk image\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem enable\-touch\-id\-sudo\fR
Enable Touch ID for sudo authentication\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem disable\-touch\-id\-sudo\fR
Disable Touch ID for sudo authentication\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem flush\-dns\fR
Flush the DNS cache\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem force\-eject\fR
Force eject a mounted volume\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem ifactive\fR
Show active network interfaces\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem reload\-autofs\fR
Reload the autofs automount daemon\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem spotlight\fR \fIquery\fR
Search using Spotlight\.
.
.SS "Linux\-specific system subcommands"
.
.TP
\fBsystem fix\-sudo\-setrlimit\-error\fR
Fix the sudo setrlimit error on Linux\.
.
.TP
\fBsystem zsh\-compaudit\-set\-permissions\fR
Fix Zsh compaudit permissions\.
.
.SH "DEVELOP SUBCOMMANDS"
.
.TP
\fBdevelop log\fR
View the latest temporary log file\.
.
.TP
\fBdevelop cache\-functions\fR
Regenerate the cached Bash function library\.
.
.TP
\fBdevelop edit\-app\-json\fR
Open \fBapp\.json\fR in the default editor\.
.
.TP
\fBdevelop format\-app\-json\fR
Sort and format \fBapp\.json\fR\.
.
.TP
\fBdevelop push\-app\-build\fR
Push a single application build to the binary cache\.
.
.TP
\fBdevelop push\-all\-app\-builds\fR
Push all application builds to the binary cache\.
.
.TP
\fBdevelop prune\-app\-binaries\fR
Remove stale application binaries from the cache\.
.
.TP
\fBdevelop roff\fR
Regenerate man pages from ronn source files\.
.
